# .shellcheckrc — Plan 23-01 (BLG-06) repo-global shellcheck disables.
# Each disable carries a one-line rationale. See
# .planning/phases/23-gha-environmental-forensics-lint-triage/23-01-FINDINGS.md
# for the per-finding audit trail (195 dispositions).

# rationale: pack/test scripts source $CKA_SIM_ROOT/lib/*.sh dynamically;
# shellcheck cannot follow $CKA_SIM_ROOT-prefixed paths. Existing per-line
# `# shellcheck source=... disable=SC1091` directives in lib/log.sh,
# tests/lib/assert.sh, and a few cases stay; this disable covers the bulk.
disable=SC1091

# rationale: same family as SC1091 — non-constant source paths
# (source "$case_file" in tests/run.sh, source "$flags" in
# packs/troubleshooting/06-broken-kubelet/grade.sh). Static analysis
# cannot validate; runtime behaviour is exercised by tests/.
disable=SC1090

# rationale: variables flagged are either (a) exported state consumed by
# sourced grade.sh / setup.sh helpers (CKA_SIM_GRADE_PASSES,
# CKA_SIM_GRADE_TRAPS, CKA_SIM_PACK_META, CKA_SIM_EXAM_*), (b) ANSI colour
# constants in lib/colors.sh consumed by every script that sources it, or
# (c) loop-counter `i` used for the side-effect of N iterations.
disable=SC2034

# rationale: single-quoted strings are deliberate literal patterns:
# `'${CKA_SIM_LAB_NS}'` for render-verbatim verification, literal grep
# patterns like `'bash "$qdir/setup.sh"'`, and printf format strings
# carrying literal UTF-8 escape sequences (`\xe2\x9c\x93`). Forcing
# double-quotes would change semantics.
disable=SC2016

# rationale: $? capture after a multi-line block ending with a pipeline
# whose rc is examined separately from structural assertions; rewriting
# as `if ! cmd; then` would change scoping and break later log-format
# assertions in uat-phase{3,4}.sh.
disable=SC2181

# rationale: `local x=$(cmd)` is a pervasive corpus idiom; the masked
# rc is intentional in cases where best-effort capture with an empty
# fallback is the documented behaviour (CONTEXT.md disposition rule
# ordering names this explicitly).
disable=SC2155
